  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. Increasing the positive quantity <span class=\"italic\">x</span> by 9% is the result of adding 9% of <span class=\"italic\">x</span> to <span class=\"italic\">x</span>. 9% of <span class=\"italic\">x</span> can be represented algebraically as <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction, 9 over 100, end fraction, times x\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"0 point 0 9 x\"></span>. Adding this expression to <span class=\"italic\">x</span> yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x plus 0 point 0 9 x\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"1 point 0 9 x\"></span>.<p>Choice B is incorrect. This represents 9% of <span class=\"italic\">x</span>. Choice C is incorrect. This represents increasing <span class=\"italic\">x</span> by 9, not by 9%. Choice D is incorrect. This represents increasing <span class=\"italic\">x</span> by 0.09, not by 9%.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
